Dear colleagues,


You are kindly invited to participate to the


*International Conference on Information Systems for Crisis Response and 
Management*

*in Mediterranean countries (ISCRAM-med 2014)***


to be held in Toulouse (France), 15-17 October, 2014.

Early registration deadline is September 15th.

The program, the registration procedure and accommodation information 
are available at:

http://irit.fr/ISCRAMMED2014

A copy of the program is also available below.

Participants will have the opportunity to attend presentations made by 
renowned keynote speakers:

*Sihem Amer-Yahia, Alexis Drogoul and Laurent Franck. *

Please, circulate this email among your colleagues and students.

Hope to meet you in Toulouse.

Conference chairs
Frédérick BENABEN, François CHAROY and Chihab HANACHI.



ISCRAM-med program
**************************

Wednesday 15 October 2014
**********************************

08:00 - 09:00        Registration

09:00 - 09:30        Opening

09:30 - 10:30        Keynote - Alexis Drogoul - Simulating the past to 
better manage the present: geo-historical modeling of past catastrophes 
in the ARCHIVES project

10:30-11:00 Break

Session Preparedness 1:  Supply chain and distribution

11:00 - 11:30        A Location-Allocation Model for More Consistent 
Humanitarian Supply Chains
M. Lauras, J. Vargas, L. Dupont, A. Charles

11:30 - 12:00        Towards Large-scale Cloud-based Emergency 
Management Simulation "SimGenis Revisited"
C. Labba, N. Bellamine Ben Saoud, K. Chine

12:00 - 12:30        Logistics Alliance Framework for Urban Emergencies 
Based on Second-Generation VBE
B. Lu, N. Mehandjiev

12:30 - 14:00        LUNCH

Session Preparedness 2:  Modeling and training

14:14:30 Approaches to optimize local evacuation maps for helping 
evacuation in case of tsunami
V.M. Le, Y. Chevaleyre, J.-D. Zucker, H. Tuong Vinh

14:30 - 15:00        EDIT: a methodology for the treatment of 
non-authoritative data in the reconstruction of disaster scenarios
S. Traverso, V. Cerutti, K. Stock, M. Jackson

15:00 - 15:30        Towards a Decision Support System for Security 
Analysis: Application to Railroad Accidents
A. Maalel, L. Mekri, H. Hadj-Mabrouk, H. Ben Ghézela

15:30 - 16:00        break

16:00 - 16:30        Crisis mobility of pedestrians: from survey to 
modelling, lessons from Lebanon and Argentina
E. Beck, J. Dugdale, H. Van Truong, C. Adam

16:30 - 17:00        Supporting debriefing with sensor data: a 
reflective approach to crisis training
S. Mora, M. Divitini

17:00 - 18:30        Demo session



Thursday 16 October 2014
*******************************

08:30 - 09:00        Registration

09:00 - 10:00        Keynote - Laurent Franck - Revisiting the Möbius 
strip: where emergency field practices and research activities meet

10:00 - 10:30        Coffee Break

Session Response 1: Human interactions on crisis field
10:30 - 11:00        Citizen Participation and social technologies: 
exploring the perspective of emergency organizations
P. Diaz, I. Aedo, S. Herranz

11:00 - 11:30        Access Control Privileges Management for Risk Areas
M. Fugini, M. Teimourikia

11:30 - 12:00        A Formal Modeling Approach for Emergency Crisis 
response in Health during Catastrophic Situation M. Ouzzif, M. Hamdani, 
H. Mountassir, M. Erradi

12:00 - 12:30        Collaborative re-ordering in Humanitarian aid networks
S. Vidolov

12:30 - 14:00        LUNCH

14:00 - 14:30        Response 2: Coordination and agility        Towards 
Better Coordination of Rescue Teams in Crisis Situations: a Promising 
ACO Algorithm - J. Mahdjoub, F. Rousseaux, E. Soulier

14:30 - 15:00        A Multi-Agent Organizational Model for a Snow Storm 
Crisis Management - I. Thabet, M. Chaawa, L. Ben Said

15:00 - 15:30        Agility of crisis response: from adaptation to 
forecast. Application to a French rod crisis management use case
A.-M. Barthe-Delanoë, G. Macé Ramète, F. Bénaben


15:30 - 16:00        Coffee Break


16:00 - 16:30        The Dewetra Platform: a multi-perspective 
architecture for risk management during emergencies
Italian Civil Protection Department, CIMA Research Foundation

16:30 - 17:00        Decision Support for Disaster Risk Management: 
Integrating Vulnerabilities into Early-Warning Systems
T. Comes, B. Mayag, E. Negre

20:00-23:00        GALA DINNER


Friday 17 October 2014
****************************

08:00 - 09:00        Registration

09:00 - 10: 00        Keynote - Sihem Amer-Yahia - Task Assignment 
Optimization in Crowdsourcing (and its applications to crisis management)

10:00 - 10:30        coffee break

Session Social aspects  in crisis management

10:30 - 11:00        Integration of emotion in evacuation simulation
V. Tho Nguyen, D. Longin, H. Tuong Vinh, B. Gaudou

11:00 - 11:30        Emotional Agent Model for Simulating and Studying 
the Impact of Emotions on the Behaviors of Civilians during Emergency 
Situations - M. Belhaj, F. Kebair, L. Ben Said

11:30 - 12:00        Emergency Situation Awareness: Twitter Case Studies
R. Power, B. Robinson, J. Colton, M. Cameron

12:00 - 13:30        LUNCH

13:30 - 14:30        CLOSING SESSION: ISCRAM Community - future of 
ISCRAM'med





